Enum DefaultAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DefaultAction>

    public enum DefaultAction
extends java.lang.Enum<DefaultAction>
implements Action
    A thing one might be permitted to do or prohibited from doing to something.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ADD

        public static final DefaultAction ADD
        This action modifies a number by adding a given value to it. This action modifies a number by adding a given value to it. The field to be modified and the given value are specified in the policy as idsc:JSONPATH/idsc:XPATH and idsc:OPERAND, respectively.

      • AGGREGATE_BY_CONSUMER

        public static final DefaultAction AGGREGATE_BY_CONSUMER
        Data will be part of another piece of data so that it is not distinguishable anymore. This action is always evaluated at the consumer side.

      • AGGREGATE_BY_PROVIDER

        public static final DefaultAction AGGREGATE_BY_PROVIDER
        Data will be part of another piece of data so that it is not distinguishable anymore. This action is always evaluated at the provider side.

      • ANONYMIZE

        public static final DefaultAction ANONYMIZE
        To anonymize all, parts or certain attributes of the resource. This action is always evaluated at the provider side.

      • COMPENSATE

        public static final DefaultAction COMPENSATE
        To pay a certain amount of money in order to use a resource. This action must be evaluated both at the consumer and provider side. A compensation might be required before access is granted (provider-side), or each time the usage action is performed (consumer-side).

      • DELETE

        public static final DefaultAction DELETE
        To remove a resource or inhibit any further access with reasonable measures. This action is evaluated at the consumer side if used in a duty clause. A provider cannot be forced to delete its data resources. If used in a permission clause, it is effecting the data provider as it allows the consumer to delete the provider's resource remotely.

      • DISTRIBUTE

        public static final DefaultAction DISTRIBUTE
        To forward or supply a resource to a third-party. This action is always evaluated at the consumer side and allows it to become a data provider of this resource.

      • DIVIDE

        public static final DefaultAction DIVIDE
        This action modifies dividing something by something else. This action modifies dividing something by something else. The field to be modified and the given value are specified in the policy as idsc:JSONPATH/idsc:XPATH and idsc:OPERAND, respectively.

      • ENCRYPT

        public static final DefaultAction ENCRYPT
        The data artifact or parts of it are encrypted and can not be read by neither the ids:DataConsumer nor any other third party. The encryption algorithm might be specified by a constraint. This action is always evaluated at the provider side.

      • GRANT_USE

        public static final DefaultAction GRANT_USE
        To grant use of a resource to another party. Does *not* imply any other usage rights. This action is always evaluated at the consumer side, at the moment a third party intends to access the resource as received by the original consumer.

      • HASH

        public static final DefaultAction HASH
        This action modifies a value by replacing it with a hash of the value. This action modifies a value by replacing it with a hash of the value. The field to be modified and the hash algorithm are specified in the policy as idsc:JSONPATH/idsc:XPATH and idsc:HASH_ALGORITHM (eg. SHA256), respectively.

      • INCREMENT_COUNTER

        public static final DefaultAction INCREMENT_COUNTER
        An action to be used in the count usage policy where the idsc:COUNT left operand is used.

      • LOG

        public static final DefaultAction LOG
        To log information or store information about incidents in a local file or database. Is not necessarily available to external parties but can be used to create transparency on happened events. This action is always evaluated at the consumer side.

      • MODIFY

        public static final DefaultAction MODIFY
        To change a resource locally. This action is always evaluated at the consumer side. It corresponds to 'allow changes of the copied resource'.

      • MULTIPLY

        public static final DefaultAction MULTIPLY
        This action modifies a number by multiplying it to a given value. This action modifies a number by multiplying it to a given value. The field to be modified and the given value are specified in the policy as idsc:JSONPATH/idsc:XPATH and idsc:OPERAND, respectively.

      • NEXT_POLICY

        public static final DefaultAction NEXT_POLICY
        To forward the resource under the same policy. Implies a permission to distribute. This action is always evaluated at the consumer side.

      • NOTIFY

        public static final DefaultAction NOTIFY
        To log information or notify an instance about incidents. Can be used to define Clearing House interactions. This action can target the consumer and the data provider of the resource.

      • READ

        public static final DefaultAction READ
        To obtain data from the resource. This action is always evaluated at the provider side. It corresponds to 'give access to a resource'.

      • REPLACE

        public static final DefaultAction REPLACE
        To replace some value. This action modifies a value by replacing it with a given value. The field to be modified and the given value are specified in the policy as idsc:JSONPATH/idsc:XPATH and idsc:REPLACE_WITH, respectively.

      • SHUFFLE

        public static final DefaultAction SHUFFLE
        This action modifies a value by replacing it with an anagram of the value. This action modifies a value by replacing it with an anagram of the value. The field to be modified is specified in the policy as idsc:JSONPATH/idsc:XPATH.

      • TRACK_PROVENANCE

        public static final DefaultAction TRACK_PROVENANCE
        To accept that the use of the Asset may be tracked. This action is always evaluated at the consumer side.

      • USE

        public static final DefaultAction USE
        To use a resource in any possible way. Includes all other actions. This action is always evaluated at the consumer side.

      • WRITE

        public static final DefaultAction WRITE
        To change a remote resource. This action is always evaluated at the provider side. It corresponds to 'allow changes of a resource' but *not* including its deletion.
